The behavior of Neumann matrices at  was first analyzed in
 by resumming all-orders power expansions in the large  (small )
limit. In manipulating with multiplications of infinite dimensional matrices 
the authors of encountered divergences which were regularized using
the zeta-function regularization. Recently inthe Neumann matrices at 
were calculated using a different method leading to manifestly regular expressions.
The results of which we use in this paper
agree with the expressions obtained at order , but 
not at higher orders in .
Two comments are in order:

1.   These perturbative expressions for the Neumann matrices should not be 
interpolated to the flat space expressions at  since essential
singularities at  were discarded.

2.  Each of the Neumann matrices is expanded in powers of ,
the odd powers of  can appear only as an overall multiplicative factor.
Hence the fractional powers of  hopefully should not appear in the
string theory prediction at higher orders, thus making a happy connection
with the gauge theory interpretation.

